# PATCH: 001-disable-screenshots
# PURPOSE: Block all screenshot capture paths — both the built-in Firefox Screenshots
#          extension and OS-level window capture hints.
#
# POLICY COVERAGE (policies.json + user.js):
#   - "DisableScreenshots": true  → disables Firefox's own Screenshots toolbar button
#   - extensions.screenshots.disabled = true → disables the built-in extension
#   DOES NOT block: OS-level capture tools (screencapture, Print Screen, OBS, etc.),
#   other extensions, or any app that calls the OS screen capture API directly.
#   The policy has no awareness of the OS windowing system.
#
# WHAT THIS PATCH MUST ADD (policy alone is insufficient):
#
# 1. browser/extensions/screenshots/background/takeScreenshot.js (JS, simpler):
#    - Find the `captureTab` and `captureSelectedArea` functions.
#    - At the top of each, add:
#        throw new Error("ZeroFox: screenshots disabled");
#    - This kills the built-in extension path even if policy is bypassed.
#
# 2. For OS-level screenshot blocking (macOS — NSWindow flag):
#    File: widget/cocoa/nsCocoaWindow.mm
#    In nsCocoaWindow::Create() or Show(), after the NSWindow is initialized, add:
#      [mWindow setSharingType:NSWindowSharingNone];
#    This prevents the window from appearing in screen capture APIs and screen recorders.
#    Reference: https://developer.apple.com/documentation/appkit/nswindowsharingtype
#
# 3. For X11/Linux (prevent MIT-SHM / XFixes screenshot):
#    File: widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp
#    In nsWindow::Create(), call:
#      gdk_window_set_composited(mGdkWindow, TRUE); // force composited, not readable
#    OR patch the X11 event loop to reject XFixesGetCursorImage and similar.
#    (This is a best-effort; X11 has no reliable screenshot-prevention mechanism.)
#
# 4. For Windows (SetWindowDisplayAffinity):
#    File: widget/windows/nsWindow.cpp
#    In nsWindow::Create() or Show(), after HWND is created:
#      SetWindowDisplayAffinity(mWnd, WDA_EXCLUDEFROMCAPTURE);
#    This makes the window appear black in all screen capture tools.
#    Requires Windows 10 2004+ (build 19041+).
#
# GENERATE THIS PATCH:
#   Make the changes above in the Firefox source tree, then:
#   cd src/firefox-<version>
#   hg diff widget/cocoa/nsCocoaWindow.mm \
#           widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp \
#           widget/windows/nsWindow.cpp \
#           browser/extensions/screenshots/background/takeScreenshot.js \
#     > patches/001-disable-screenshots.patch
